social_posts.post_text: Some appropriately ❄️❄️❄️ vibes coming out of the studio.  We’re almost calling it a wrap on this weird/hard/wonderful/challenging/incredibly busy year for this little biz. It’s been a lot! We’ve made so many beautiful things I’ve been hoarding! Hoping to spend some time in the next couple weeks just reflecting and organizing and making plans and space for all the goodness in 2023. I hope all of y’all get some cozy, special, quiet time and a break or at least a really good cocktail and some proper treats this season. I’m heading out West with my fam for the snowiest holiday these little sunbelt bebes can handle. Big hugs and lots of love to all of you 💙💙💙 #inkandindigostudio

2022 in art! And truly this is not even close to all of it - just working from what I had on my phone on a flight with no internet 😂 More grateful than ever for this gig and these friends, clients, pups, and all the peeps I don’t have pics of that make this work so special. What a time! 💙💙💙#inkandindigostudio #carveouttimeforart #artistmother #artistmotherco #atlantaartist #hospitalityart #hospitalitydesign #creativityfound #abmlifeiscolorful #sodomino #dscolor #artstudio #studioscenes #workinprogress #hotelart #interiordesign #madeinthesouth #acolorstory #encaustic #rfencaustic #encausticpainting #encausticart

Cutie new install pic of a commission we just completed for the fab @ginasimsdesigns project @waltonfayetteville. Love that these paperclay cuppies have lives allll over in so many different formats and styles. While we often do these as direct-to-wall installations they work really well on panel too. | paperclay cuppies in natural clay and custom colors on cradled wood panels, 48”x36” each #inkandindigostudio

We’ve been prepping so many elements for so many big things for so many weeks and hot dog I’m excited to actually start bringing it all together! My brain really can’t process one more unfinished thing! These blues are for a large scale oval clay strata-a first of this body of work in that format and I think it will be beautiful. Cheers to a new week babes. #inkandindigostudio 💙

Just wrapped this series of 36 paperclay, botanical inlaid discs today and we are IN LOVE. These were commissioned for a site in the desert so we included prickly pear + agave + all the desert inspired, stabby beauties we could find to roll into clay mid winter in the South!  Each is about 12” dia and finished with fire, watercolor, and encaustic wax. I really want you to be able to pet them as they are just sooo delish but maybe will just have to share like 8000 more photos ✨🌵🏜️💙💙💙#inkandindigostudio #sculpturalart #dimensionalart #carveouttimeforart #artistmotherco #atlantaartist #hospitalitydesign #hospitalitydesigners #hospitalityart #artstudio #studioscenes #hotelart #interiordesign #madeinthesouth #installationart #wallsculpture #dscolor #interiordesigninspirations #residentialdesign #paperclay #sculpture #encaustic #encausticartist #botanicalart

A few more glamour shots of these desert destined bebes because I just love them so. 36 pieces, 12”dia each, cacti/botanicals inlaid into paperclay, flame burnished, water colored, and sealed with encaustic wax and a lil bit of magic ✨ #inkandindigostudio (no idea why the last pic repeated three times but just roll with it 😂)
New fave 💙💙💙 oval format of my Strata style in mega layers of Japanese paperclay finished in rich watercolor blues | 42”H x 84”W #inkandindigostudio
Studio boys so perfectly captured today by our @samkrayons 💙💙💙 #inkandindigostudio
A real ✂️✂️✂️ + 🎉🎉🎉 situation in the studio today #inkandindigostudio

It’s school auction season (kid people I know you feel me) and I’ve been helping to collaborate & coordinate with our kiddo’s school to create some mega cool art projects! Peeks at a few I’ve been wrapping up that will be up for auction this week💙💙💙 #inkandindigostudio

A little behind-the-scenes and dorking about in the making of a giant, custom blue “Burst” for our fav @whitakerartconsulting recent project in Chevy Chase, Maryland. This one is huge-72” diameter and it took lots of testing and sampling to get just right. It is composed of thousands of hand-plastered, painted, cut, and attached “petals” we make from reclaimed canvas. RIP to my shoulder socket but ain’t she pretty?! Big ups to our pal @diamondbackartsurfaces for not only creating all our substrates but making moving this beast possible!  And to @nonvisiblearts for getting it there and installed beautifully 💙 #inkandindigostudio #sculpturalart #dimensionalart #carveouttimeforart #atlantaartist #hospitalitydesign #hospitalityart #artstudio #studioscenes #hotelart #interiordesign #installationart #wallsculpture #textileart

A good ol’ fashioned, non-moving pic of this piece for us old-timers who simply cannot with all the reels 🧘 Also! Unsolicited advice (?) for my fellow artists-I get inquiries alllll the time from clients referencing my Instagram even going waaaay back in the grid. So if (like me) you really can’t put the time into the IG daily grind it’s still worth putting up pics of your actual work, when you can-regardless of algorithms and whatnot. I still find a lot of inspo and creativity here but I’ll never be able to play the IG game like it wants us to! So make it work for you! 😘 | 72”dia canvas, plaster, and painted “Burst” dimensional wall work | all gratitude to @whitakerartconsulting for the commission 💙 #inkandindigostudio

Working from home with a sick kiddo (thankfully on the mend!) and just really enjoying the quiet and light of my house. Sounds weird but I hardly get to hang here during weekdays and man, it feels good! Taking advantage of the non-garish overhead lighting (one day I will have good studio lighting, it’s top of mind!) to show you this new encaustic piece in my “Overtone” style. These are created from building up and scraping away dozens of layers of pigmented and clear encaustic wax-with gentle torch fusing between layers. It’s magical and unpredictable and there’s a depth to it that can really only be appreciated in person. This is 24”x24”-twice as big as others and feels like a little blue pool to dive into. Love. | All of the pieces in my Overtone series are available for fine art licensing on my site-all the deets are there or reach out if interested 💙#inkandindigostudio

These are giving green + gold + magic and if that’s not apropos for ☘️☘️☘️ I dunno what is! This series of 6 is an addition to my larger Venture Vesica line. I was forcing myself to use what I had on hand to make new work-pulling from the flat file gold mines and finding assorted pigment and ink paintings and vellum from previous projects. I covered vellum in metallic gold line work, played around with protractors and circle cutters and just went to town collaging. Sticking with a general theme and format but then working outwards from there is such a good way to generate new ideas and make something that feels fresh but cohesive with a larger body of work. I love how these turned out and they reproduce *perfectly*! All these + so many more are in the licensing line and I would love love love to see them out in the world so just holla if you need more deets! 💙 #inkandindigostudio

So rainy and chilly here! I had all the best intentions of getting my yard sorted and finally planning a summer garden this spring break but will be indoorsing real hard instead. Just scored this Eames beauty from a consignment shop for cheeeeap! All it needed was some magic eraser love and now have a cat proof seating situation started. They made it their job to try to destroy two vintage Danish leather chairs I had here so I’ve been on the hunt. Need one more that works for this space and then y’all can come over for brunch mmkay? 💙💙💙

Sweet + simple sakura blooms cut into the thickest, most beautiful watercolor paper, a subtly Spring piece for today 🌸 Hope this has been a lovely weekend for all of ya celebrating Easter and Passover and those of use who are just melodramatic about SPRING!! + Cadbury mini eggs + spiffy outfits + feasting with friends and fam + the most marvelous of walking seasons…it’s just the best. I think I’ve absorbed just enough vitamin D and family time and I’m très excited to get back to the studio and make some art tomorrow! 💙 #inkandindigostudio
Custom samples heading out for a new client (+ my giant pink feets) ✨🪩✨#inkandindigostudio
Freshly completed “Portal” series commission | paperclay and watercolor assemblage in custom metal frame | 56” dia of pure 🌀💙✨ #inkandindigostudio

A bit of soft beauty for you this morning 🩵 These are from my “Atmospheres” series-14 new works available in my fine art licensing line of over 250 images. The originals are collaged watercolor, vellum, and gilded paper. Obsessively cut, layered, rearranged a thousand times, and lovingly hand detailed with metallic gold. All of these are available on my site-just message or email for details #inkandindigostudio

Happy, happy Friday peeps! A recently installed original dimensional wall work-an abstract on canvas with hand stitched clay “droplets” for our friends @lvl_design_studio + a few in-process and materials testing pics. I LOVED making this-as you can see we tested out a few different directions before landing on this muted green and mix of coordinating and natural clay. Love how subtle and soft it is- gives me ideas for lots of new things. 💚 #inkandindigostudio

Shocking but true…I also work in pastel colors! I have literally had people ask if I only work in blues (?!) 😐 A quick scroll could answer that… but truly we love playing with palettes and pretty much everything I make can be custom colored. We can pull color inspo from design boards, Pantones, paint fans, or just tell us the vibe and we’ll play! Currently mixing up some beachy peachy + sea softies for a big new installation for our peeps @dacartconsulting 🐚🍑🌊🌅 #inkandindigostudio

Ahhh! So excited that the episode I recorded of Made Remarkable @maderemarkable with my friend Kellee Wynne @kelleewynnestudios is LIVE! We kept it very real and although I was hella nervous to record it was SO FUN and easy and further proof I just need to get over myself sometimes 😂 We talk all about working with Art Consultants and Interior Designers (my main client base-I love you guys!), how I built a thriving, creative art biz without being tied to social media (but hey, I also love you guys!), showing up for what you believe in as a human who owns a business (hard but worthy and I def don’t have it figured out just yet), and so much more. I’m pretty sure I swear a lot because I simply cannot help myself 😬 Thanks so much for having me Kellee and I really hope this is the first of many convos! Link to episode is in the @maderemarkable feed and I’ll post in my stories! #inkandindigostudio #podcastersofinstagram #podcastlife #podcastforwomen #podcasthost #artpodcast #artpreneur #creativepodcast #creativebusiness #creativeempire #artbusiness

Good Morning from Ink + Indigo 💙 This is what walking into work you love looks like! Some big finished commissions, small scale client samples in the works, and 2 giant batches of dimensional wall installations in process, test prints from my fine art licensing line…This is the best gig 💙 #inkandindigostudio #studioscenes

Sometimes a commission is so challenging to complete that it can take a while to fully appreciate what the end product is and oh BABY was this one tough! I’m just now revisiting this 12 foot long assemblage from more than 6 months ago as I work on a write-up about the process and methods we used to create this custom version of my “Lamina” series. This piece is made of thousands of individually crafted and mounted paperclay “tiles” that we then painted with a funky, textile inspired pattern-a wedding of two of my most favorite things. So grateful for amazing clients who still made it an incredibly fun and respectful process that resulted in a piece that in the end is just really beautiful and different. Interested in commissioning an Ink + Indigo original for your very big or even totally normal scaled space? 😂 Just email info@inkandindigo.com and let’s make some magic ✨ | custom “Lamina” paperclay assemblage with watercolor overlay, 24” h x 144”w #inkandindigostudio

No new flavors without time in the kitchen! Had a stupidly fun time sharing my Friday freeforall in the studio-just testing out some new ideas for a client commission with encaustics + image transfers + plants + failures + chaos! Loved sharing in my stories and many thanks to y’all for cheering on this 🧛! #inkandindigostudio #studioscenes #encausticpainting #rfencaustic

Variations on a theme 💙🩵💙 We’ve been working on some custom paperclay cuppies for a possible new direct-to-wall oceanside installation. I vote yes! Love the subtly different vibe that just swaths and washier applications of color give these. #inkandindigostudio

Look at those beautiful blue babies! The time warp is reaaaal…I’ve been trying to find some pics of older work and found this from my first outside-my-house studio here at @littletreeartstudios. Somehow this was FIVE! years ago which is messing with my head. Getting a studio space was monumental (and scary at the time!) and opened up a world of possibilities for Ink + Indigo. We’ve since moved spaces and expanded in soooo many ways-fav parts being the humans and puppies I work with everyday. Making work at massive scale without losing my mind is nice too. 💙 #inkandindigostudio

Behind the scenes peek into the making of some GIANT suspended textile-y sculptures for @lvl_design_studio with a massive assist from the most best carpenter on the block Zach @diamondbackartsurfaces . So much unseen noodling and labor goes into the work we make here-this is just a tiny + hopefully fun insight into the process. This project was such a fun challenge and fingers crossed it’s the first of many more! Can’t wait to see these big bebes installed! #inkandindigostudio

Monday mission includes inbox wrangling and watering the 80000 studio plants. The news this weekend has been absolutely brutal-I’m including contacting my reps on my to-do list. Sending everyone love from right here in the #inkandindigostudio 🩵

This Cali Sunset Series is one of my favorite things I made last year. Just simple and warm and maybe a little retro which are all things that make me happy. The originals are watercolor and gouache on watercolor paper but they’re all available through my fine art licensing line so can be reproduced on pretty much any substrate, any size-allll the possibilities! All the info for our consulting and interior designer peeps is in the licensing portion of my site or hit me up with any q’s! 💙 #inkandindigostudio

Encaustics are calllling! Had the best time making a whole series of really bright and funky abstracts using my fav @sennelier1887 pigments and @rfpaints a couple of months ago and I’m ready to just be locked away for a few weeks so I can revisit and play. Not everything (or even most things) I make end up on here or into my portfolio but I just keep making so I can keep making 🙃 Somehow, someday it all comes together 💙 #inkandindigostudio

Seeing a little peek of this series recently installed right here in my hood by @canvas_atlanta prompted me to share the finished commission. These are custom botanical inlaid paperclay disks with flame torched and copper leaf details and encaustic finish. Series of 12 at 12" dia each. The details are where it’s at on these 💙 #inkandindigostudio

Hang out with me for 30 seconds on a perfectly rainy solo Friday at #inkandindigostudio 🥰 Prototyping new ideas, testing materials, and generally noodling about 💙 #studioscenes #artstudio #dimensionalart #textileart

A little behind the scenes in the studio today. We’ve been working on a ton of different things here-custom dimensional works, samples of totally new series yet to be revealed, and wrapping up some big ‘ol commissions. Feels really good to zone out and get back to one of my classics-painting with pigments a la my #100daysofinkandindigo series. Playing with darker pigments and trying (not yet succeeding) to get the *just* right flow for what we have in mind. #inkandindigostudio

Smalls is my entire vibe today. Shoutout to my fellow migraine suffering peeps-even 30 years in I’m still shocked to get taken down as hard as I do sometimes! So opting for soft pants and catching up on heaps of computering that didn’t happen last week and A+++ snuggles with this earth angel. #inkandindigostudio

Our friends @kalisher_studio shared an install pic of these beauties yesterday which made me realize I never shared them here! A trio of large scale, flowing paperclay “Petal” assemblages at 72” x 36” each beautifully framed and installed at AC Jackson Ridgeland. This is my fav format for these-something about the large vertical series format just…💋 We can make these in pretty much any size, finish, and format so they work beautifully on a range of projects-alllll the info for commissioning is on my site 💙#inkandindigostudio

I’m just a girl (fine! a middle aged woman) standing in front of REALLY big print of her own work, asking….how have I not gotten to design wallpaper yet???? For reals though-seeing these massive giclees of my work makes me think for the approximately 1000000 X that I would LOVE to create wallpaper with my designs. Anyone know how to do dis? Tell me all your secrets! Also would you buy my wallpaper? 😂 💙💙💙#inkandindigostudio

Totally justifiable reason to keep every single shell I find this week right? 😂 (video is my torching process on some custom dimensional paperclay elements with 🐚 sealife impressions) #inkandindigostudio
pure inspiration, taking it all with me 💙  #inkandindigostudio

Couldn’t sleep so I made ya something 🙃 💙 Little #inkandindigostudio vid of the indigo pigment painting process…as many times as I’ve made these it’s still ✨magic✨ This original was part of a custom series for a hospitality project but I have so many more available in my fine art licensing line and of course can always create custom commissions-it’s kinda my jam. Alllll the links in bio 💙💙💙

The Indigo Strokes are a fav version of my pigment flow paintings-combining dynamic bold brush strokes with the sort of unpredictable pigments…a bit of beautiful chaos contained ✨ This series is part of my fine art licensing line so can be printed on pretty much any substrate at any size and would be so fab as a large scale series in a hotel public space or something snazzy. They work equally well solo-one large framed statement piece could be really impactful. All of these (and 250+ other images) available on the fine art licensing portion of my site-linked above! #inkandindigostudio 💙💙💙

Sometimes photos of my installed work actually exist and then…I forget to share them 🫠 Was reminded of this Droplets installation at the gorgeous, fancy pants @rooftop_loa here in town. @art_initiative_atl  created a beautiful art package for the project-we loved collaborating with them to create this custom installation. These suspended paperclay droplets can be done in any color palette, scale, and arrangement-this spans about 12 feet. Lemme know if you spot any I + I in the wild! It’s still a thrill everytime! 💙 #inkandindigostudio
Such plumage 🩵🩵🩵 #inkandindigostudio
Sweetest clay cuppies sample- customizing these forever favorites with soft sea tones and iridescent overlays for a beach casa direct-to-wall installation. Dream gig! #inkandindigostudio

Dear ones! Did you know I only share an itty bit of all the #inkandindigostudio happenings here in zuckland? I send Studio News 2X a month mostly for our dear client collectors in art consulting + interior design but everyone is welcome! I’m REALLY excited to be adding new offerings and resources for my fellow creatives-sharing insider info on running a professional art studio, working in my sweet lil (big) niche, art materials and methods, and creative inspo I think you’ll love. I’ll be sharing courses and workshops and all the goodness I’ve been thinking on and learning the hard way for almost 20 years! (don’t do the math, I’m a tiny baby) Just make sure you indicate what you’re into at sign up so I have you on the right list. First Ink + Indigo Studio Creative Consulting Newsletter goes out tomorrow afternoon so signup at the link in my bio! 🩵

Happy, happy Friday peeps. Sharing these cuties from my “Flora” series-an ongoing collection of simple plant studies and some funkier patterned numbers inspired by so many of the absolutely bonkers botanicals we obsessed over on a trip to Hawaii. Plants are my other true love-my studio and my home are filled with SO many and somehow never enough 😂My veg garden is sorta languishing this year and mostly a massive win for the squirrel and chipmunk population of Atlanta 🫠 ANYHOOTS. I am working behind the scenes on some new pieces for the licensing line and am def going to add more Flora! All of these + 250 more images are available in my fine art licensing line-perfect for all kinds of hospitality, residential, corporate, and healthcare design projects. All the details on how to use + order are at the link in my bio 💙#inkandindigostudio

Few things more satisfying and energy shifting than a massive cleanup and reorganization and we’ve been doing just that with our supply zone here in the studio this week. Revisiting projects and pieces is fun and helps me appreciate just how freaking hard and long I’ve been working at this biz! 😂  Checkout all these handmade clay feathers I created for a project at the Peabody Memphis with @dacartconsulting a few years ago. The Peabody is famous for its daily duck March so of course the feathers are a nod to their little icons 🦆I had a one woman feather factory set up to roll, cut and detail each one. They were mounted in groupings and framed. So fun. 💙 #inkandindigostudio

Go bid on one of my original encaustic pieces! I donated this beeswaxy beauty from my Hiss + Hum series to benefit the @wyldecenter-one of my happy places and an absolute greenspace haven + incredible community resource here in Decatur + Atlanta. Their annual Beer Garden auction is happening right now and closes tomorrow June 24th at 7:30 pm. Proceeds directly fund their environmental + garden education program that teaches more than 8000 metro Atlanta kids. You don’t have to be present to win so follow link on their page or in my stories to bid. I included pics of my own Wylde loving child making her own encaustic piece and a little vid of the process behind these works for funsies 💙 #inkandindigostudio

A mini Portal sample cutie…as much as I love them mega sized…they are so sweet at this size too! 💙 A big part of working on custom, large scale dimensional artworks is being comfortable making small scale samples that are representative of the work and gives everyone on the client side a common language and understanding of what will be delivered BEFORE the job is underway. For a lot of projects this means my own investment costs on the front end but over lotsa years I’ve seen the return in exciting commissions and repeat clients. Plus we really do just love making tiny things 💙  #inkandindigostudio
more summer blues 💙 #inkandindigostudio

So many ways to bring a sense of place into the custom artwork we create and one of my favs is being able to pull in plant life specific to the project location. We recently completed a custom series of inlaid botanical clay works for a project in Colorado Springs and we were able to reflect that using some of the Columbine, Aspen, Pine, and Cedar that can be found in the area. The color palette was directed by the design and mood boards and I love how this pushed a bit outside the cooler tones we are often commissioned to do. Want to see how we can create something special just for your project? It’s kind of my thing! Drop me a line anytime  via link in bio or email emily@inkandindigo.com 💙| custom inlaid botanical paperclay disks, flame burnished, watercolor finish with encaustic seal, approx 6-12" diameter each | #inkandindigostudio

I didn’t really plan on setting up my home studio again (it’s been about 5 years since I moved out!) but loose kid schedules have made it impossible to get long stretches in the actual studio this week.  Having this as an option is really so lovely. I’m making several samples for a big new project where I’ll be doing 16 large encaustic works on circular panels and I have to test what methods I can use to get the look I’ve achieved before but at much larger scale + qty. For a lot of what I do actually making the thing is the only way to know exactly how to make the thing 😉 My subterranean setup is extra appreciated since it’s about a billion degrees out today + it stays coooool down here. How are my fellow creatives faring this summer? 💙 #inkandindigostudio
Hi hi and happy, happy Friday babes. Some things I made this week that I simply love 🤍💙🩵 #inkandindigostudio
So many favs: thrifted shirt + new dream @bryrclogs + flea market antique rug + most beautiful kitty 💙
Loving this duo color wool felt assemblage currently in the works at ye olde #inkandindigostudio 💛💛💛
Perks 💙#inkandindigostudio

Taking advantage of our current very Barbie moment to share some just for fun encaustic explorations in the pinkest pinks and fluorescents I made a while back -these just might be inspired by my most prized Barbie outfit of alltime-United Colors of Benneton oversized sweatshirt, insane leggings, and coordinating hat 😂! Please swipe for that 1990 goodness. God I wanted this in my size. I haven’t seen the movie yet but love hearing all the reviews and appreciation for just how weird and fun and fem. Heading out for a camping trip which is a uniquely bad idea in 1000000 degree weather but going to try to summon some *fun mom* Barbie energy and eat a s’more! Happy, happy Friday peeps 💕💕💕#inkandindigostudio

Cute candy colored art situation happening here in the studio 🍭🩷❤️🧡💛💚🩵💙 The fun sized “Ribbons” series are client samples and this colorful variation on our “Disk” series on panel is a test of concept that we’re all loving. #inkandindigostudio

Embellishing these gorgeous massive!!! reproductions of my work with a weeks worth of careful hand painting and stitching gold elements ✨✨✨ All the thanks to our steady handed queen @dearalphabet for getting these bars *just so* and our dear client @whitakerartconsulting for the push to try something new! #inkandindigostudio PS BEYONCE TONIGHT BAYBEEEEES!!!

My friend, artist, and coach Lea Ann Slotkin @leaannslotkin has launched a brand new podcast called Mind Over Medium where she is exploring mindset for creative success + more! So tickled that today’s ep features yours truly! We chatted all things Ink + Indigo, creative process, pushing past discomfort, goal setting, and not taking yourself too dang seriously. We also discussed Smalls Mann and how really this account could use more dog content. 😂 It’s available on allll the platforms and through the link in my stories. Thanks for having me Lea Ann! Go listen! #inkandindigostudio

Just been a lil busy 😂🫠💅🏼 We’ve got so much in the works-clay installation pieces, massive string art, a huge order of original encaustics, a birch + encaustic assemblage…all the tings! Attempting to get my head back in the sharing game after wonky summer hours, a back to school bout of the ‘vid, and many side quests! 💙 #inkandindigostudio
Client meeting prep is the cutest 💙 #inkandindigostudio
Tiny bebe chichi for scale! Whole studio is fully freaking out about how good these string art pieces for @lvl_design_studio are turning out. So. Excited. #inkandindigostudio

Selfiereporting that I’m officially brown haired again-my profile photo is a lie! 😂 How we doin?? This has been a FULL on week and I’m so ready to hermit! There is a lot of cool new shiz in the works and I’m going to try real hard to actually share it here okee? My forever struggle! Anyhoo hope everyone is hanging on and not melting.  Happy happy Friday peeps💙#inkandindigostudio
Love this variation on a well-loved Ink + Indigo  theme 💙 Simple floralesque cut paper on heavyweight watercolor wash for our dear @nancysokolove  #inkandindigostudio

New love 💚💚💚 Custom 60” dia paperclay “Portal” in ferngulliest greens for a gorgeous project with @kevinbarryartadvisory. Painstaking but worth it-each clay element is cut, painted and assembled by hand into the beautiful metal frames @diamondbackartsurfaces makes for us. A biophilic beauty. #inkandindigostudio #dimensionalart #hospitalitydesign #wallsculpture

Non-moving pics to immortalize this beauty 🍃One of my fav things about collaborating with consultants and designers is the constant push to iterate, innovate, and play with different scale, color ways, and formats. Always feels good to arrive at something that feels *just right* like this 60” dia custom Portal for @kevinbarryartadvisory in deep leafy greens. Each paperclay element is cut, painted and assembled by hand into this beautiful metal frame by @diamondbackartsurfaces. Can’t wait to see this one in its home  #inkandindigostudio 💚💚💚

New custom commission I absolutely love - a Lamina beauty in indigo and natural paperclay for @kevinbarryartadvisory 💙 | 24”H x 72”W paperclay with watercolor finish on cradled wood panel #inkandindigostudio
🤍🤍🤍work in progress ☁️☁️☁️ #inkandindigostudio
Tiny fox overseer 🦊 This massive layout of custom paperclay Droplets is challenging the limits of our studio space-going to be so good installed though! #inkandindigostudio
October is for short distance big moves! Time to pack #inkandindigostudio coming soon to @globe.arts.center 💙
